channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: US retail sales ticked up last month in sign of ongoing consumer resilience
item.description: Americans spent a bit more at retailers last month, providing a small boost to the economy just as the Federal Reserve considers how much to cut its key interest rate

item.title: What Investors Need To Know Ahead Of The Tesla Robotaxi Event
Sean "Diddy" Combs arrested by federal agents in New York
item.description: Sean "Diddy" Combs has been arrested in New York and is in federal custody. The arrest follows nearly a dozen lawsuits, most of which have accused Combs of sexual assault. Combs has settled one of the cases and denied the allegations. The charges he was arrested on have not yet been released.

item.title: Sean 'Diddy' Combs hit with sex trafficking charges in sprawling indictment
item.description: Sean "Diddy" Combs has been charged with sex trafficking by force, transportation to engage in prostitution and racketeering conspiracy.

item.title: Sean 'Diddy' Combs charged with racketeering, sex trafficking
Dozens of Hezbollah members reportedly injured by exploding pagers
item.description: Dozens of Hezbollah members were reportedly injured when their pagers exploded in the Iran-backed group's Beirut and south Lebanon strongholds.

Hamas chief silent on Israel's offer of escape in exchange for hostages
item.description: Israel's hostage coordinator tells CBS News that Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar could leave Gaza with his family if the hostages are released.

item.title: Facebook owner Meta bans Russia state media outlets over 'foreign interference'
item.description: Meta is banning Russia state media organization from its social media company platforms, alleging that the outlets used deceptive tactics to amplify Moscow’s propaganda

item.title: Over-priced Fed rate cuts make T-bills unattractive, Federated Hermes says
Widow of man killed in Baltimore bridge collapse speaks out, calls for better safety protections
item.description: It's been nearly half a year since a cargo ship slammed into Baltimore's Key Bridge, causing its collapse and the deaths of six workers on the bridge. As some of the victims' families announce a legal claim against the ship's owner, the widow of one of the workers, Maria del Carmen Castellon, is opening up about the tragedy.

item.title: China says it tailed a US spy plane through the sensitive Taiwan Strait
item.description: Chinese warplanes tailed a U.S. military aircraft through the sensitive Taiwan Strait on Tuesday, China’s military said
